At best this is a wasted move. We have all made this move - once. The reasons why not - 1. it encourages white to develop while defending easily by 0-0  2.  N is vulnerable here and will have to spend another move to get back to f6 (two free moves for white) 3. it loses N and a pawn for B if white plays Bxf7  4. it neglects development  for an inconclusive attack

The blunder that kills off black. Any other Q move works (sort of !) (except QxN) but the discovered check was obvious, so its a matter of looking at the possible damage a free N move can cause (really, white can cash-in his 2 free moves here). Kg6 lost at least a piece but Qf8 turned it into loss of Q.
